langchain-huggingface is the official partner package designed to provide a seamless bridge between the LangChain orchestration framework and the Hugging Face ecosystem.
As of 2026, this package has completely replaced the older integrations that used to live inside langchain-community. If you see tutorials mentioning from langchain.llms import HuggingFaceHub, those are outdated—you should now use this dedicated library for better performance and support for the latest models.
1. Installation
You need to install the partner package along with the Hugging Face Hub library.
pip install langchain-huggingface huggingface_hub

2. Key Components
The library is divided into three main ways to interact with models:
A. Local Execution (HuggingFacePipeline)
Use this when you want to run a model locally using your own hardware (RAM/GPU). It uses the transformers library under the hood.
 * Best for: Privacy, offline use, and maximum control.
 * Requirement: Sufficient local VRAM/RAM.
B. Remote Inference (HuggingFaceEndpoint)
Use this to call models hosted on Hugging Face’s infrastructure (Serverless Inference API or Dedicated Endpoints).
 * Best for: Fast prototyping, low local hardware, and production-grade scaling.
 * Requirement: A Hugging Face API Token.
C. Embeddings (HuggingFaceEmbeddings)
This is the most common use case. It allows you to use sentence-transformers locally to turn text into vectors for your RAG pipelines.
3. Code Example: Local vs. Remote
Using a Remote Endpoint (Cloud)
from langchain_huggingface import HuggingFaceEndpoint

# Initialize the remote model (e.g., Mistral-7B)
llm = HuggingFaceEndpoint(
    repo_id="mistralai/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3",
    task="text-generation",
    max_new_tokens=512,
    huggingfacehub_api_token="your_token_here"
)

response = llm.invoke("What are the benefits of open-source AI?")
print(response)

Using Local Embeddings
from langchain_huggingface import HuggingFaceEmbeddings

# This downloads the model to your cache and runs it on your CPU/GPU
embeddings = HuggingFaceEmbeddings(model_name="all-MiniLM-L6-v2")

vector = embeddings.embed_query("Hugging Face and LangChain work great together.")
print(f"Dimension size: {len(vector)}") # 384

4. Why Use the Partner Package in 2026?
| Feature | langchain-huggingface | Old langchain-community |
|---|---|---|
| Model Support | Supports latest Qwen, Llama 3, and Mistral. | Often buggy with new architectures. |
| Quantization | Built-in support for 4-bit and 8-bit loading. | Requires manual transformers config. |
| Tokenization | Uses fast Rust-based tokenizers by default. | Slower Python-based tokenizers. |
| Chat Interface | Includes ChatHuggingFace for chat-specific models. | Mostly basic text completion. |
> Wit's End: Switching to langchain-huggingface is like upgrading from a universal remote to a dedicated smart-home hub. It just understands the devices (models) much better.
